Undeads roles (Latest update):

Ghoul - Currently this is an umbrella term for 3 roles that a host can put into their setup (Hungry Ghoul - Starts on N1 with a kill power; Perceptive Ghoul - Starts with a check power; Cunning Ghoul - Starts with a stalk power). Ghoul is able to “feed” on a dead body and gain either a kill, check or stalk power. Until the Ghoul uses this power,, they cannot “feed” on another dead body. If the ghoul feeds on a fellow undead member who’s in GY, the Ghoul assumes that exact role for the rest of the game.
VD - Refer to H2P, there are no changes implemented on this role.
Necromancer - Refer to H2P as well. Only tweak to this role is that a necromancer is seen as a WC user.
Medium - No changes. Refer to H2P.

Banshee - Banshee is a role that activates it’s power upon being killed (the way a banshee dies doesn’t affect the activation itself, but it affects when the power can be used). After the banshee dies, they are able to possess any living player the morning after their death. Every night, the banshee returns to the GY and is able to possess any other player the next morning. This continues for the length of the game. Banshee is also seen as a WC user.
